cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.NE 

This paper involves the use of deep learning techniques to predict stress levels in students using wearable devices. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of sensors and data analysis, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also has potential clinical applications, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves the prediction of behavioural states, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
